===Noun===
'''anthroposophy'''

# Also known as "spiritual science," the system of knowledge originally researched and presented by [[w:Rudolf Steiner|Rudolf Steiner]], founded as a movement after his German branch of the Theosophical Society was expelled from the international Theosophical Society; it maintains that objective knowledge of the spiritual world may be attained by any healthy human being through training and discipline.